## Core Principles (Yours Too)

- **Fix what you find.** No workarounds, no "fix later," no severity-based skip. If you can't fix now, file a proper bug — don't hand-wave.
- **Plan before you build.** Use plan mode for non-trivial work. Drive to complete PVR / A&D / Plan before implementation.
- **Commit via skills.** `/iteration-complete`, `/phase-complete`, `/git-safe-commit` — never raw `git commit`.
- **Never push without permission.** `/sync` and `/release` are the only push paths.
- **Merge, never rebase.** Hookify enforces this.
- **Handoff via the tool.** `/handoff` rotates and archives — never write `handoff.md` by hand.
- **QG before PR.** Full parallel QG + QGR receipt — not just a lone `/code-review`.

